refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
&style.oop;
public boolIntlCalendar::setFirstDayOfWeek intdayOfWeek
&style.procedural;
boolintlcal_set_first_day_of_week IntlCalendarcalendar intdayOfWeek
Defines the day of week deemed to start the week. This affects the behavior of fields that depend on the concept of week start and end such as IntlCalendar::FIELD_WEEK_OF_YEAR and IntlCalendar::FIELD_YEAR_WOY.

&reftitle.parameters;
calendar
&intl.parameter.intl-calendar;
dayOfWeek
One of the constants IntlCalendar::DOW_SUNDAY, IntlCalendar::DOW_MONDAY, â€¦, IntlCalendar::DOW_SATURDAY.

  &reftitle.examples;



   IntlCalendar::setFirstDayOfWeek


<?php
ini_set('date.timezone', 'Europe/Lisbon');
ini_set('intl.default_locale', 'es_ES');

$cal = IntlCalendar::createInstance();
$cal->set(2013, 5 /* June */, 30); // A Sunday

var_dump($cal->getFirstDayOfWeek()); // 2 (Monday)

echo IntlDateFormatter::formatObject($cal, <<<EOD
'local day of week: 'cc'
week of month    : 'W'
week of year     : 'ww
EOD
), "\n";

$cal->setFirstDayOfWeek(IntlCalendar::DOW_SUNDAY);

echo IntlDateFormatter::formatObject($cal, <<<EOD
'local day of week: 'cc'
week of month    : 'W'
week of year     : 'ww
EOD
), "\n";


    &example.outputs;


int(2)
local day of week: 7
week of month    : 4
week of year     : 26
local day of week: 1
week of month    : 5
week of year     : 27
